 the CMB+BAO+SN+$H_{0}$ data\ncombination than that using the CMB+BAO+SN data combination, and $\\beta>0$ is\nfavored at more than 1$\\sigma$ level when using CMB+BAO+SN+$H_{0}$ data\ncombination. The issue of the $H_{0}$ tension is also discussed in this paper.\nWe find that, compared with the $\\Lambda$CDM+$\\sum m_{\\nu}$ model, the $H_{0}$\ntension can be alleviated in the I$\\Lambda$CDM+$\\sum m_{\\nu}$ model to some\nextent.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 May 2020 11:37:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-16"}
